OL,6,FWhen the inquiry ended in 2014 it
OL,7,Ffound that Hamid Al-Sweady had been
OL,8,Fkilled "outright" whilst fighting, and
OL,9,Fhad been a "willing and active"
OL,10,Fparticipant in an attack on British
OL,11,Fforces. It concluded that the most
OL,12,Fserious claims of murder and torture
OL,13,Fwere "entirely false" and the product
OL,14,Fof "deliberate lies".
OL,16,FHowever, it did find that nine Iraqi
OL,17,Fdetainees had been ill-treated.
