OL,4,CIraq war fraud
OL,6,FThe Al-Sweady inquiry into allegations
OL,7,Fof mistreatment and unlawful killing
OL,8,Fof Iraqi nationals by British troops
OL,9,Fin 2004 cost the taxpayer #24 million.
OL,11,FAccording to the NCA, Shiner received
OL,12,Faround #3 million as part of the
OL,13,Fcontract representing alleged victims.
OL,15,FDuring sentencing on Tuesday, Judge
OL,16,FHehir told the court: "The defendant
OL,17,Fisn't being sentenced for anything
OL,18,Fthat happened at the Al-Sweady
OL,19,Finquiry, nor can it be said the
OL,20,Fjudicial proceedings of the Al-Sweady
OL,21,Finquiry in any sense represent harm."
